discussion with professor eduardo brondizio center for latin american studies jump to navigation stanford university center for latin american studies search this site home events discussion with professor eduardo brondizio discussion with professor eduardo brondizio monday december 12 2011 1 30pm 2 30pm the working group on perspectives of sustainable development in latin america would like to invite students to a discussion with professor eduardo brondizio over coffee and cookies in preparation for his colloquium at the anthropology department later that day this discussion is part of a series that the working group organizes with faculty and activists from a range of disciplines that work in the broad field of sustainable livelihoods conservation and political ecology in latin america the gatherings are informal but engaging we facilitate a discussion seeking to understand speakers personal perspectives on work vision and career path join us if you are a student seeking to learn how to transition from academics into activism while in and when out of school eduardo brondizio is professor and chair of the department of anthropology associate director of the anthropological center for training and research on global environmental change act and faculty associate with the workshop with the workshop in political theory and policy analysis at indiana university bloomington eduardo brondizio professor and chair of the department of anthropology indiana university bloomington bolivar house 582 alvarado row last updated january 25 2012 10 58am calendar main menu about degree programs visiting faculty & scholar programs grants & fellowships people events newsletter giving to clas secondary menu stanford home ica clasp login contact stanford university center for latin american studies bolivar house 582 alvarado row stanford ca 94305 usa phone 650.723 4444 fax 650.723 9822 stanford university terms of use copyright complaints
